  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p><i>α</i>-Terpinene, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>16</sub>, is a pleasant-smelling hydrocarbon that has been isolated from oil of marjoram. On hydrogenation over a palladium catalyst, <i>α</i>-terpinene reacts with 2 molar equivalents of H<sub>2</sub> to yield a hydrocarbon, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>20</sub>. On ozonolysis, followed by reduction with zinc and acetic acid, <i>α</i>-terpinene yields two products, glyoxal and 6-methyl-2,5-heptanedione.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcVFTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a283ab2d98b9726e6ecab514a3dfe1c8bdb9da61/OChem_08_EC_048.jpg\" alt=\"The structures of glyoxal and 6-methyl-2,5-heptanedione.\">",
